 <text>
  <front>
   <head>The Revenge of AMERICA.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHEN fierce PISARRO'S legions flew</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O'er ravag'd fields of rich Peru,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Struck with his bleeding people's woes,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Old India's aweful Genius rose.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He sat on Andes' topmost stone,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And heard a thousand nations groan;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For grief his feathery crown he tore,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To see huge PLATA foam with gore;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He broke his arrows, stampt the ground,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To view his cities smoaking round.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">What woes, he cry'd, hath lust of gold</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O'er my poor country widely roll'd;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Plunderers proceed! my bowels tear,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But ye shall meet destruction there;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">From the deep-vaulted mine shall rise</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Th' insatiate fiend, pale Avarice!</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whose steps shall trembling Justice fly,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Peace, Order, Law, and Amity!</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I see all Europe's children curst</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With lucre's universal thirst:</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The rage that sweeps my sons away,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">My baneful gold shall well repay.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
